<HEADLINE>
<P>
FUZZY LOGIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I wonder if perhaps the only thing fuzzy is Kosko's scientific perception and 
understanding. There is nothing inherently wrong with Western theorizing. 
</P>
<P>
Western science purports that every continuum in science and nature, whether it 
be the transition from hot to cold or from heavy to light rain, can be 
described as a function, or a system of functions, based on a series of yes or 
no responses. 
</P>
<P>
Kosko states: "I'd be the biggest atheist that ever lived." As the term atheist 
is itself absolute, is this not an extreme attitude for one who does not deal 
with either/or interpretations? 
</P>
<P>
For goodness' sake, Bart, turn down the heat in the hot tub, even if it's a 
little bit at a time. 
</P>
<P>
MARVIN W. KIST, Regina, Sask. 
</P>
</TEXT>
