146 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENT PAPERBACKS: IF THE RIVER WAS WHISKEY BY T. CORAGHESSAN BOYLE (PENGUIN: 
$7.95) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Like teddy bears wrapped in barbed wire, the characters in T. Coraghessan 
Boyle's award-winning collection of short stories conceal an aching 
vulnerability behind a thorny shield. Boyle is an often devastating commentator 
on Los Angeles and the weirdos, wanna-bes and mountebanks who congregate here. 
</P>
<P>
A down-and-out immigrant stunt man risks mutilation and death to achieve 
fleeting immortality in the supermarket tabloids. A sleazy press agent faces 
the monumental task of improving the Ayatollah's public image. A 
security-system saleswoman preys on yuppie paranoia with carefully orchestrated 
stories of psychotic attackers: A murder she inadvertently provokes becomes the 
choicest grist for her mill. This acerbic, scrupulously observed portrait of 
contemporary Southern California is apt to confirm the reader's most dire 
suspicions about the people next door. 
</P>
</TEXT>
