<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENT PAPERBACKS: CAUGHT IN A STILL PLACE BY JONATHAN LERNER (SERPENT'S TAIL: 
$9.95) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A weird, almost hallucinogenic novel of post-apocalyptic life in the Florida 
Keys. Government has collapsed, leaving Jonathan Lerner's bizarre cast of 
characters struggling half-heartedly to preserve the guttering flame of 
civilization. Lerner seems to be offering a testament to the enduring powers of 
love and friendship, but the two get rather muddled when a gay man and a 
heterosexual woman inexplicably decide to become bedmates. 
</P>
