</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
'DR. WELSING IS THE FIRST SCIENTIST TO PSYCHOANALYZE WHITE RACISM. . . .' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beyond the scientific information on color dominance, whites also emulate black 
people in terms of what we do and say and how we look. 
</P>
<P>
For instance, the bustle worn by whites was inspired by the prominent buttocks 
of black women (i.e., Hottentot sculpture and other images in the 17th and 18th 
Centuries in Europe); dances and phases and gestures invented by blacks are 
immediately snatched and adopted by whites. 
</P>
<P>
I believe melanin has a great deal to do with the association of blacks with 
having more soul, rhythm and coordination. 
</P>
<P>
If I were white and read the Cress Theory and the other scientific information 
on melanin (such as "Melanin: The Chemical Key to Black Greatness" by Carol 
Barnes, chemist), I'd not only want to look, act and sound black as many whites 
already try to do -- I'd want to be black. 
</P>
<P>
SUESAN COLEMAN 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
