circle after Preakness. Associated Press; Photo, (A2) Stretching Out: Summer 
Squall, who had a bleeding problem Friday, rallied in the stretch to 
beatKentucky Derby winner Unbridled by 2 1/4 lengths in the Preakness at 
Baltimore. 
</P>
