<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIXED MEDIA; 
</P>
<P>
* 1/2 "ROCK ART: THE MOODY BLUES" AEON HOME VIDEO. ($19.95): WORKS ARE RATED ON 
A SCALE OF ONE STAR (POOR) TO FIVE STARS (A CLASSIC). 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This is a psychedelic version of one of those insufferably soothing New Age 
videos that feature serene nature scenes accompanied by tranquil instrumental 
music. 
</P>
<P>
In this half-hour video, colorful, constantly-changing geometric shapes pulse 
and cavort to the rhythms of melodic old Moody Blues tunes, like "Nights in 
White Satin." As a psychedelic light show, it's often mesmerizing -- certainly 
much more exciting than those boring New Age videos. The problem, though, is 
those bland Moody Blues oldies, which are probably only of interest to those 
feeling nostalgic about the hippie era. The best way to watch this video is to 
turn down the sound and add your own soundtrack. DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, "The Moody Blues" video, right. 
