<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SANTA PAULA; 
</P>
<P>
HEARING FOCUSES ON LEVY TO SAVE OPEN SPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JANET BERGAMO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Santa Paula City Council will hold a public hearing Monday on an assessment 
district to maintain open space in the new Hillsborough tract. 
</P>
<P>
The tract of upscale housing in north Santa Paula, where houses cost at least 
$395,000, is in the first phase of construction. 
</P>
<P>
The open space, including a flood-control basin and a grove of trees, must be 
maintained under an agreement made between the developers and the city when the 
69-house project was approved in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
The cost of maintaining the basin and landscaping is to be borne by homeowners 
in the tract. An assessment of about $100 annually would appear on the property 
tax bill. 
</P>
<P>
Wilkinson emphasized that surrounding homeowners would not pay for the proposed 
assessment district. JANET BERGAMO 
</P>
