<HEADLINE>
<P>
SECTION HIGH SCHOOL SOFTBALL; 
</P>
<P>
HILLTOP'S HILL THROWS 4TH NO-HITTER OF SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hilltop's Jackie Hill became the fifth pitcher in San Diego Section history to 
throw four no-hitters in a season, leading her team into the second round of 
the 3-A softball playoffs Saturday with a 5-1 victory over Mira Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
Hill, a junior, walked three and struck out seven. She had previous no-hitters 
against Lincoln, Grossmont and Montgomery. 
</P>
<P>
The Lancers committed two errors, one of which allowed Mira Mesa to score an 
unearned run in the top of the first inning. 
</P>
<P>
Hill dominated offensively as well with four of her team's six hits. 
</P>
<P>
Other pitchers to throw as many as four no-hitters in a season are Santana's 
Cheryl Forehand (1979), Patrick Henry's Donna Stiles (1984), San Marcos' 
Celeste Sanchez (1987) and Castle Park's Dawn Wood (1988). 
</P>
<P>
In other 3-A playoff games: 
</P>
<P>
Southwest 2, El Capitan 0 (10) -- Melle Esquivel gave up nine hits, but 
Southwest (13-11) took advantage of two hits, two errors and two wild pitches 
in the final inning to upset second-seeded El Capitan (20-6). 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Buena Vista 3, Morse 2 -- Venus Moll's two-out squeeze bunt scored 
Annjanette Vittulli with the winning run in the fifth. Rachel Boyer (19-5) 
allowed just five hits. Top-seeded Rancho Buena Vista (22-5) committed six 
errors, allowing Morse (13-9) two unearned runs. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Glen 2, Mar Vista 1 (11) -- Gina Phillips' inside-the-park home run gave 
Orange Glen (15-8) the victory. Lara Campbell (15-8) had a career-high 17 
strikeouts and walked just one. Mar Vista (15-8) scored an unearned run in the 
first inning, Orange Glen scored an unearned run in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel 1, Patrick Henry 0 -- Stacy Thimjon's two-out single for Mt. Carmel 
(20-4) drove in winning pitcher Jennifer Ortiz (17-2) in the fourth inning. 
Ortiz allowed four hits and struck out eight. Patrick Henry finished 12-13. 
</P>
<P>
Chula Vista 1, Vista 0 (9) -- Armida Medina's single in the bottom of the ninth 
scored Cathy Slatinsky. Medina went two for four for Chula Vista (19-8). Vista 
finished 14-12. 
</P>
<P>
Serra 3, Bonita Vista 0 -- Desiree Wallace (11-5) pitched a six-hitter and No. 
4 Serra (13-11) took advantage of four Bonita Vista errors to score three 
unearned runs. Stephanie MacLeod and Sherry Pierce drove in one run apiece. 
Bonita Vista finished 10-9. 
</P>
<P>
Granite Hills 4, Poway 3 -- Granite Hills scored four unearned runs, including 
two in the bottom of the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
Division 2-A 
</P>
<P>
San Marcos 8, University City 1 -- Sophomore Charlene Reyes homered, singled, 
tripled and drove in three runs, and allowed just one hit through six innings, 
striking out nine while improving to 14-4. Missy Anguiano added two hits and 
two RBIs for the Knights (23-5). University City finished 12-10. 
</P>
<P>
Madison 7, Our Lady of Peace 0 -- Jenifer Booker pitched a one-hitter and 
struck out 14 as top-seeded Madison (25-3) beat Our Lady of Peace (9-10). Dawn 
Sanphy, Suzanne Galleta and Booker had two hits apiece. 
</P>
<P>
Santana 7, San Diego 0 -- Shelly Hawkins pitched a one-hitter and struck out 11 
for No. 2 Santana (26-2). Deann Ford was two for two with three runs, and 
Cristy Stippey was three for four for the Sultans. 
</P>
<P>
USDHS 3, El Camino 0 -- Vicki Vechinski pitched a two-hitter as No. 4 USDHS 
(17-6) defeated El Camino (10-12). 
</P>
<P>
Mission Bay 4, Christian 1 -- Heidi Leach had a two-run double, and Margaret 
Johnson was two for three with an RBI for Mission Bay (13-8). Christian 
finished 14-10. 
</P>
<P>
Escondido 6, Clairemont 0 -- Escondido improved to 18-6 with the shutout of 
Clairemont (13-7). 
</P>
<P>
Carlsbad 2, El Cajon Valley 1 (8) -- Renee Demirdjian squeezed home the winning 
run in the top of the eighth for Carlsbad (12-11). Winning pitcher Monica 
Sharpe struck out eight. El Cajon Valley finished 13-12. 
</P>
<P>
Valhalla 3, San Pasqual 1 -- Kellie Stone pitched a three-hitter and struck out 
seven as Valhalla (9-16) upset San Pasqual (21-6). Stacey Terrien had two hits, 
and Shaney Eardley and Arminda Gonzalez each had a hit and an RBI. 
</P>
<P>
Division 1-A 
</P>
<P>
La Jolla Country Day 14, Imperial 3 -- Allison Griffith was four for four with 
four runs and an RBI, and Kate Pyle was three for five with five RBIs as LJCD 
(12-8) upset No. 3 Imperial (13-6) at Imperial. Annje McFarland (9-7) pitched a 
two-hitter. 
</P>
<P>
Calvin Christian 11, Francis Parker 6 -- Second-seeded Calvin Christian (17-4) 
will meet Imperial in the semifinals Thursday. Francis Parker finished 7-15. 
</P>
<P>
Mountain Empire 9, Borrego Springs 1 -- No. 4 Mountain Empire (21-5) advanced 
to Thursday's semifinals, where it will meet top-seeded Bishop's (19-3), which 
had a first-round bye. 
</P>
