<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL NEWS: POMONA PARENT PROJECT RECEIVES HONORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Youth Authority has honored the Pomona Parent Project, a 
collaborative effort of Pomona Police Department and Pomona Unified School 
District designed to reach parents of at-risk youth. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Ralph Fry received the Distinguished Service Award, and the district 
received the Outstanding Program for Youth Award. 
</P>
<P>
The project offers parents four weekly sessions providing information on tough 
discipline techniques, gang awareness, drug and alcohol abuse prevention, and 
school success. 
</P>
</TEXT>
