<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE COMPLAINT BOARD PANELISTS SOUGHT IN L.B. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Applications are being sought for positions on the new 11-member Citizen Police 
Complaint Commission. 
</P>
<P>
The panel will receive and investigate allegations of police misconduct, with 
emphasis on excessive force, false arrest, and complaints with racial or sexual 
overtones. 
</P>
<P>
It will also conduct hearings into allegations of police misconduct and 
subpoena witnesses and other materials as necessary. 
</P>
<P>
Members will be appointed by the mayor, subject to the confirmation by the City 
Council, with one member appointed to represent each of the nine City Council 
districts and two at-large representatives. 
</P>
<P>
Applications are available at City Hall, 333 W. Ocean Blvd. 
</P>
