<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST: FOR DEDICATED GARDENERS, HERE ARE SUGGESTIONS FROM THE 
CALIFORNIA ASSN. OF NURSERYMEN ON WHAT TO DO IN THE GARDEN THIS WEEK: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Divide crowded clumps of bearded iris after the bloom is finished. 
</P>
<P>
This should be done every third year or so. 
</P>
<P>
If you have bedding plants waiting to be transplanted into the garden, remember 
to keep them watered. 
</P>
<P>
Garden-fresh herbs can add more flavor to your outdoor barbecuing. Plant them 
in pots near the barbecue area to have them close at hand while cooking. 
</P>
<P>
Shallow-rooted plants like camellias, rhododendrons, azaleas and fuchsias will 
benefit from a thick application of mulch to conserve moisture and keep roots 
cool. 
</P>
</TEXT>
