<HEADLINE>
<P>
E. CONTINI'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was deeply saddened to learn of Edgardo Contini's death. He was far more than 
an architect. 
</P>
<P>
He was a colleague from the UCLA campus. In a development community 
characterized by glitz and slickness, he personified charm and class. It was 
always a delight to interact with him, even when he was on the other side of 
the bargaining table. He brought intelligence, dignity, patience, wit and a 
quiet strength to the process of development. He will be sorely missed. 
</P>
<P>
LAURA LAKE 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
Editor's Note: Edgardo Contini died April 28 at age 76. His obituary was 
published in Section A of The Times on May 1. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
