<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOME BUYERS FAIR; 
</P>
<P>
CONSUMER PROTECTION; 
</P>
<P>
FREE GUIDE ON HOME INSPECTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The engineering department of Aetna Life &amp; Casualty has created a free home 
inspection guide, "Before a House Becomes a Home." 
</P>
<P>
The booklet tells home buyers what to look for when they're looking over a 
prospective house -- and when to have the house inspected by a professional. 
</P>
<P>
Some hints: Check exterior of the house for wood rot; check for missing 
shingles on the roof; look for cracks and water stains in the ceilings and 
walls that may indicate leaking plumbing fixtures or a leaky roof. 
</P>
<P>
For a copy of the booklet, write: Aetna Life &amp; Casualty, Resources RWAC, 
151 Farmington Ave., Hartford, Conn. 06156. 
